na"/> || S. Krishna Sharma || 1965 || Mysore state, India |- |Vaishnavism || ''Sriramapattabhisheka''<ref name="prabhu"/><ref name="medha"/><ref name="patta">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), p178</ref> || [[Masti Venkatesha Iyengar|Masti]] || 1972 || Mysore state, India |- |Secular || ''Bharatasindhu rashmi''<ref name="sindhu">Rao in Datta (1988), p1183, chapter-Epic(Kannada)</ref><ref name="rash">K.M. George (1992), p672</ref> || [[V.K. Gokak]] || 1982 || Karnataka state, India |- |Secular || ''Bhavyamanava''<ref name="sindhu"/> || S.S.Bhusanurematha || 1983 || Karnataka state, India |- |} {| class="wikitable sortable" |+ Extinct epics in the Kannada language known from quotes and references by later writers |- ! bgcolor=#99CCFF | Faith ! bgcolor=#99CCFF | Epic ! bgcolor=#99CCFF | Author ! bgcolor=#99CCFF | Year ! bgcolor=#99CCFF | Patron |- |Jainism |''Chandraprabhapurana''<ref name="chandra1">Narasimhacharya (1988), pp.17-18</ref> || Srivijaya || 9th century ||Rashtrakuta Empire |- |Jainism |''Karnata Kumarasambhava''<ref name="karkumara">Dash & Pattanaik in Paul St-Pierre & Prafulla C. Kar, (2007), p.167</ref><ref name="upa">Warder A.K. (1988), p.241</ref><ref name="champ">Sahitya Akademi (1987), pp618-619</ref> || [[Asaga]] || 853 ||Rashtrakuta Empire |- |Jainism |''Harivamsha'' (''Neminathapurana'')<ref name="karkumara"/><ref name="champ"/><ref name="matter">Warder A.K. (1988), p240</ref><ref name="harinemi">Rice E.P. (1921), p30</ref> || [[Gunavarma I]] || 900 ||Western Ganga Dynasty |- |Jainism |''Shudraka''<ref name="karkumara"/><ref name="champ"/><ref name="matter">Warder A.K. (1988), p240</ref><ref name="harinemi">Rice E.P. (1921), p30</ref> || Gunavarma I || 900 ||Western Ganga Dynasty |- |Secular || '' Bhuvanaika-Ramabhyudaya'' (''Ramakatha'')<ref name="shanti"/><ref name="spurana"/><ref name="katha">Garg (1992), p67</ref> || Sri Ponna || 950 || Rashtrakuta Empire |- |Jainism || ''Parasurama Charita''<ref name="shanti"/><ref name="parasu">Kamath (1980), p114</ref> || Ranna || 980-990 || Western Ganga Dynasty |- |Jainism || ''Chakreshvara Charita''<ref name="shanti"/><ref name="chakra">Kamath (1980), p45</ref> || Ranna || 980-990 || Western Ganga Dynasty |- |Shaivism || ''Hariharamahatva''<ref name="harish"/><ref name="char"/> || Raghavanka || early 13th century || Hoysala Empire |- |Shaivism || ''Sharabacharite''<ref name="harish"/><ref name="char"/> || Raghavanka || early 13th century || Hoysala Empire |- |}
