{{Infobox language |name = Omok |nativename = |states = [[Russia]] |region = [[Sakha Republic|Yakutia]] and [[Magadan Oblast]] |extinct = 18th century or earlier |ref=linglist |familycolor = Palaeosiberian |fam1 = [[Yukaghir languages|Yukaghir]] |iso3 = omk |glotto=yuka1240 |glottorefname=Yukaghir Omok |linglist = omk }}
'''Omok''' is an extinct [[Yukaghir language]] of Siberia, part of a [[dialect continuum]] with the two surviving languages. It was last spoken perhaps as late as the 18th century.
